Consumes HP/SP/Stamina can be recovered through the following options.
Spontaneous Recovery is slow compared to other recovery methods, but it does not require the player to do anything.
[Potion Recovery] : Recover HP/SP/Stamina immediately using potions.
Potions have cooldown times before you can re-use.
[Tree Root Crystal] : Destroy Tree Root Crystals to recover Stamina.
Tree Root Crystals are randomly generated around the field.
[Rest Mode] : Using the bonfire during Rest Mode speeds up your recovery.
Recovery in Rest mode is faster than Natural recovery and it is even faster if you use bonfire during Rest mode.

Swordsmans are warriors who have strong physical abilities. They use various weapons to deal with enemies up close at the front line.
Highlanders are tough fighters and use two-hand swords. They make enemies ccollide with each other or terrains so they are great for handling multiple enemies.
Peltastas are defensive warriors who use shields to block enemy attacks and provoke the enemy.
Hoplites use spears with long range attacks. They gain bonus when fighting against strong enemies that are at larger than mid-size.
Centurions command the battle with formations.
Barbarians are reckless and aggressive warriors who are not bound to any formats in battle and would do anything to claim victory in their hands.
Cataphracts use two hand spears. They are cavalries who break through and grind the enemy barriers.
Rodeleros ambush and disintegrate enemies. Their defensive skills using shields are effective for blocking long range attacks.
Wizards use magic to block attacks or to protect themselves. They can make powerful and concentrated attacks for a single target or area of effect attacks for multiple enemies.
Pyromancers use continuous fire magic to fight against multiple enemies.
Cryomancers use ice magic to freeze enemies or protect allies from enemies by using ice walls.
Psychokinos use psychokinesis to control gravity, or pull and throw away enemies.
Sorcerers summon devils and controls them.
Linkers link allies together to reduce the damage received or connect enemies to amplify the damages.
Necromancers collect and use dead parts of monsters.
Thaumaturges use magic that change attributes and formation of enemies. They can shrink enemies or strengthen allies to help the battle.
Elementalists use the magic power of elements. They can make powerful magic attacks but have a cooldown time so it is important to cooperate with others.
Archers use bows and various secondary equipments. Their specialties are long range and moving attacks.
Hunters are trainers who hunt enemies using companions. Companions hunt using skills that require cooperation with its owner such as biting and holding onto enemies or finding hidden targets.
Quarrel Shooters use shield and crossbow for a strategic combat. They can defend from long range attacks and use catapault skills against approaching enemies.
Rangers are specialized in fighting against multiple enemies through quick, long range attacks.
Sappers are archers who intall traps and lure the enemies to the traps to attack.
Wugushis specialize in using various poisons to attack or bewitch the enemies.
Scouts specialize in reconnaissance and infiltration. They use stealth to hide themselves and convey enemy's situation to allies for an advantage in leading the battle.
Clerics heal and protect allies through the blessings of the Goddess, while knocking down the enemies with strong blows
Priests are clerics who give blessings and ressurrect the dead with their holy powers.
Krivis are priests who use the fire to help recovery of allies or give strong damage to the enemy.
Bokors use voodoo skills to turn the dead to zombies or curse the enemies to attack them from afar.
Sadhu can use their soul to disappear from the enemies or convey their powers to other players.
Dievdirbys carve and place the holy statues. The statues protect allies or attack the enemies.
Monks are clerics who train in martial arts through the blessing of the Goddess.
Pardoners are clerics who don't deny to be blessed by the Goddess with their wealth.
Paladins use their holy power to protect allies and vanquish enemies through the blessings of the Goddess.

Use the arrow keys to move your character.
The Strength stat increases your physical damage and critical damage.
The Vitality stat increases your max HP, HP recovery rate, inventory weight, critical resistance and shield block rate.
The Intelligence stat increases your magic attack.
The Spirit stat increases your max SP and SP recovery rate.
The Dexterity stat increases your accuracy, critical chance and avodability.
Hold down Z to attack continuously.
When your STA has reached 0, you will stop running.
Destroy Tree Roots Crystals in fields or use Stamina Pills to recover your STA.
When the monster is the same level and attack damage is twice the monster's HP, overkill is triggered and you earn bonus EXP.
Press the Insert key to rest. In rest mode, your HP, SP and STA recovery increases.
When nearby a bonfire in rest mode, the recovery of all characters resting will increase.
You can craft items in rest mode if you have the recipes and materials.
Use the anvil to enhance your weapons and armor to become stronger.
The Potential of an item decreases by player trading, adding sockets, equipping magic amulets or failing enhancement.
Press the Enter key to open the chatting window. After you're done chatting, press Enter again to close the window.
Entering /y before your chat allows you to broadcast your message. The Megaphone item is required to do so.
You can repair equipments with low durability through the blacksmiths located in town.
You can buy and sell items through the merchants in town.
You can return to the quest NPC immediately by using the 'Backspace' key or pressing the 'Go back' button.
You can learn job-specific attributes from the Master NPCs. Look for the Master NPC's in each area.
Shiny Monsters can drop items up to more than ten times than normal monsters.
Various merchants and master NPC for each class are located in a village.
You can move to other areas through Goddess Vakarine Statue.
You can move to other areas using the Warp Scroll if there is no Goddess Vakarine Statue nearby.
During your adventure, you can find hidden treasure chests. Some treasure chests may require keys that match the level.
Press F12 to record a gameplay video.
Press Print Screen to take screenshots.
Press F1 to view your character information.
Press F2 to open your inventory to see the items and silver you own.
Press F1 to view info on your class, skills, and attributes.
Press F4 to view your cumulative record of gameplay.
Press F5 to view information on quests in progress.
Press F6 to view your party.
Right click on another player's character to send a party request. When the request is accepted, you can play together in a party.
It shows the list of current parties in the game. Click on the list to join the party.
Press F7 to view your buddy list.
Press F8 to apply a pose or macro.
Press F9 to view the current status of your Companion.
Press F10 to view the help list.
You can adopt or train Companions through the Companion Merchant NPC.
Right-click on another player to make trade requests.
Press M to view the current area map.
Press N to view the world map.
The durability of equipped items decreases once the character becomes incapable of combat.
When you reach max class level, you can Advance to the same or different class.
Use the mission item purchased from the mercenary commision to open the portal and enter mission.

Monsters have 1 of the 6 elemental attributes : Fire, Ice, Earth, Darkness, Poison or Electric.
Attacking with countering properties of each monster can cause more damage.
Press and hold the attack button to continuously attack the enemy in target. You can also move while attacking using the arrow keys.
Archer's arrow attacks have maximum range. Higher damage is made when shot from a distance.

Basic range attack of Archers cause more damage to flying monsters.

When Wizard type classes level up, Magic defense increases.
When Warrior type classes level up, Physical defense increases.

Highlanders are tough fighters who use two-hand swords. They make enemies ccollide with each other or terrains so they are great for handling multiple enemies.
Centurions command the battle with formations. They control other soldiers to use different formations depending on the situation.
Corsairs for their party into Pirate group and use unique tactics. They can steal enemy's items, get treasure chests, and use combo system.
Doppeldoeldners are mercenaries who endure high risk for high rewards. They dangerously expose themselves to the enemies and receive high attack power or high EXP.
Squires are warriors who support fellow soldiers. They support by repairing and enhancing others' weapons or intall basecamp to aid the team.
Alchemists use alchemy to enhance gem and synthesize or craft items.
Sorcerers are wizards who summon the devil. They control or ride the summoned devil to fight against enemies.
Cronomancers are wizards who control time. They stop, speed up, or change back time to help fellow soldiers.
Necromancers are wizards who use dead body parts. They attack or make summons using the dead body parts collected.
Rogues are combat professionals that can do anything for victory. They specialize in ambush from behind enemies using catapault and sword, or using arrows during stealth.
Schwaze Reiters maneuver quickly. They specialize in diverse shooting techniques using pistol.
Fletchers make and use special arrows. Various arrows result to powerful attacks depending on the type of enemy and combat situation.
Eung-sa controls the Hawk. Hawks amay be fussy abut they become reliable companions when trained well.
Druids are clerics that use the power of nature. They control the grass to help allies of transform into monsters and use monsters's skill.
Oracles are priests that use foresight. They can predict or interfere with enemy's attacks and determine their fate.
